parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or catch fire, leading to accidents, injuries, and property damage.
symptoms: The ignition switch is extremely hot to the touch
and may lead to smoke or fire under the hood or dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The limitation on fuel tank filling can cause inconvenience, increased fuel stops, and potentially lead to running out of fuel, which can leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel tank will only fill up halfway
the fuel pump shuts off prematurely
the fuel tank cannot be filled to its full capacity.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation and blowout can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
Brake failure can lead to a loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
brake failure when coming down steep grades
